From: Tim Huang <Tim.Huang@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 6 May 2024 16:30:01 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu: fix mc_data out-of-bounds read warning
Git-commit: 51dfc0a4d609fe700750a62f41447f01b8c9ea50
Patch-mainline: v6.11-rc1
References: CVE-2024-46722 bsc#1230712

Clear warning that read mc_data[i-1] may out-of-bounds.

Signed-off-by: Tim Huang <Tim.Huang@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_atombios.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_atombios.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_atombios.c
@@ -1625,6 +1625,8 @@ int amdgpu_atombios_init_mc_reg_table(st
 										(u32)le32_to_cpu(*((u32 *)reg_data + j));
 									j++;
 								} else if ((reg_table->mc_reg_address[i].pre_reg_data & LOW_NIBBLE_MASK) == DATA_EQU_PREV) {
+									if (i == 0)
+										continue;
 									reg_table->mc_reg_table_entry[num_ranges].mc_data[i] =
 										reg_table->mc_reg_table_entry[num_ranges].mc_data[i - 1];
 								}
